node.text:
I am very excited to introduce The Tanlah collection which is inspired by my indigenous roots in the Chuvash Culture. Tanlah means equality and is inspired by traditional Chuvash symbols for duality, good and evil, life and death, and helping one another.
Chuvash is one of many indigenous groups of people who were colonized and are now part of Russia (190 distinct indigenous groups survived colonization in Russia and still suffer from colonization, ethnophobia and racism). While growing up I was conditioned to be ashamed of myself and my culture, it is a colonial tactic done to many indigenous people to sever connection to our ancestors and earth and assimilate the culture. It is very powerful to reconnect to your heritage and an important decolonization tool. Now I always wear jewelry with the Tanlah symbol to remind me of that, and I hope to inspire you to do the same. -Al

node.text:
Custom made 14k yellow gold & diamonds engagement and wedding ring set. 

We can make your custom piece with your stones but prefer to work with ours. This way, we can provide a warranty for the stones as well as the jewelry. With stones from other sources, we are not responsible for any damage to the stone. We can acquire almost any stone for you which will include a warranty and a cheaper price than if you were to buy a stone separately from somewhere else.

node.text:
Exactly the same stones, 2 completely different designs - check out these engagement rings we made for a couple. Both have .75ct diamond in the center with blue and teal sapphire as side stones.
Create your own customized jewelry piece with us! We are open for custom orders and can make your jewelry with any stones. Visit our custom page on our website to start your inquiry.

node.text:
I often get asked what inspires my designs, here is my attempt to answer that question. 
Also did you know that this is #nonbinaryweek and I am super happy to be here and be visible. It took me 29 years to come out as enby, and while I wish I realized it sooner, I am glad to finally be my true self!
